description.narrative: This activity (Ghana Revenue Reform Programme-Technical Assistence) is a component of Ghana Revenue Reform Programme reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £4,272,204. This component benefits Ghana, and works in the following sector(s): Domestic revenue mobilisation, Democratic participation and civil society. , with the following implementing partners: AECOM, CABINET OFFICE, Coffey International Development, DAI Europe, Ernst & Young, HM Revenue and Customs, IMC Worldwide, KPMG East Africa, PwC Ghana. The start date is 01-05-2015 and the end date is 31-12-2020.
